derivation.yuyuan_name: late 17th cent.: from French, or from medieval Latin incontestabilis, from in- 'no' + contestabilis 'able to be called upon in witness', from the verb contestari (see contest)

means.word_mean: 1. incapable of being contested or disputed
2. not open to question; obviously true;
